&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re hiring a Director of Data to lead First Connect&#39;s data function and build our data into a&lt;br&gt;real competitive moat. You&#39;ll report to the CPO, manage and grow our lean data team, and&lt;br&gt;partner across the leadership table. The role is roughly 70% Build &amp;amp; Operate, 30% Lead &amp;amp;&lt;br&gt;Influence in year one, shifting toward 50/50 as the team scales.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About First Connect&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;First Connect is an insurance marketplace and aggregator. We connect thousands of&lt;br&gt;independent insurance agencies with a wide network of carriers, MGAs, and wholesalers. We&lt;br&gt;sit at a vantage point neither agents nor carriers have on their own, and turning that asymmetric&lt;br&gt;view into proprietary intelligence is one of the most important things we&#39;ll do over the next&lt;br&gt;several years.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you&#39;ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;• Lead and grow our data team. Set direction, raise the bar, make their job better.&lt;br&gt;• Make self-service analytics real across First Connect, so every leader gets to their&lt;br&gt;answers without queuing behind the data team.&lt;br&gt;• Create a contracts-based partnership with the engineering teams producing source data.&lt;br&gt;• Build a core proprietary data asset that powers our internal and partner-facing&lt;br&gt;experiences and anchors real conversations with our carriers.&lt;br&gt;• Own the data infrastructure roadmap and the question of how we evolve our data&lt;br&gt;engineering investment over the next 12–24 months.&lt;br&gt;• Define how AI gets leveraged across our data stack and analytical workflows.&lt;br&gt;• Be the data partner the leadership team actually wants to call.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who you are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;• You&#39;ve led a data team inside a startup. You&#39;re a player-coach, comfortable&lt;br&gt;writing SQL one day, pushing back on C-level the next. Startup experience is essential.&lt;br&gt;• You operate via contracts with source teams, not central ownership of every dataset.&lt;br&gt;You&#39;ve held source teams accountable for data quality.&lt;br&gt;• You&#39;re technically broad enough to make warehouse, ELT, and orchestration decisions.&lt;br&gt;Fluent in the modern data stack: a major BI tool (Sigma, Looker, Mode, Hex), dbt,&lt;br&gt;Postgres or Snowflake or BigQuery or Redshift, ingestion tooling like Fivetran.&lt;br&gt;• You have a real point of view on AI in data work and can describe what you&#39;d try first.&lt;br&gt;• You connect data investments to revenue, cost, retention, and competitive position. You&lt;br&gt;bring questions, not just answers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Nice to have&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;Insurance, Insurtech, or marketplace experience. Direct experience standing up a modern BI&lt;br&gt;platform.&lt;/p&gt;

